{"type":"message","id":"1b62d2f8","parentId":"8d48e38a","timestamp":"2026-03-06T03:06:48.371Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that there have been tasks about x402 status checking. Let me also look at recent work in Temujin's workspace and check for any generated code files.\n\nI should also check if there's any actual x402 code that has been generated. Let me look at the Parse project structure or check if there are any x402 files in the workspace.\n\nFrom what I can see:\n1. There have been tasks asking about x402 status (which are meta-questions)\n2. There's a design document in shared-context\n3. Mongke has a pending high-priority task to validate x402 claims\n\nBut I need to know if actual code has been generated. Let me check Temujin's workspace files and see if there's any implementation work.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_162abbe8713641cdaf6f5cb1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/workspace/task-1772766009.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_37513dd6e7e14626bf63a9c3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/workspace/task-1772763248.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a5b108cd97b04028b65798a7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents -type f \\( -name \"*x402*\" -o -name \"*payment*\" \\) -name \"*.ts\" -o -name \"*.tsx\" -o -name \"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":20195,"output":293,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23880,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772766392390}}
{"type":"message","id":"931819b3","parentId":"1b62d2f8","timestamp":"2026-03-06T03:06:48.436Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_162abbe8713641cdaf6f5cb1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Task Result\n\n**Task:** Parse agent implementation status and next steps\n\n**Model:** claude-code\n\n---\n\n## Parse for Agents — Implementation Status\n\n**TL;DR:** The API is **live and functional** at `parseforagents.dev` with 43/43 tests passing. Core features are complete. The x402 payment system is coded but disabled. There are 10 uncommitted files.\n\n### What's Done\n\n| Area | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| **Core API** (analyze, evaluate, chat) | Complete, live on Railway |\n| **Auth** (API keys, rate limiting) | Complete |\n| **LLM integration** (OpenRouter) | Complete with retry logic, streaming |\n| **Media analysis** (3 depth levels, 10 agents) | Complete |\n| **Test suite** (43 tests) | 100% passing |\n| **Dashboard & docs** | Complete |\n| **Docker + Railway deployment** | Complete |\n| **Security headers** | Complete |\n| **x402 payment code** | ~85% done, feature-flagged off |\n\n### What's Not Done / Needs Attention\n\n**Immediate:**\n1. **Commit pending changes** — 10 modified + 4 untracked files (test suite, x402, payment ledger, security hardening) sitting uncommitted\n2. **Deploy updated code** — Current Railway deploy is behind local\n\n**Short-term:**\n3. **Persistent storage** — Everything is in-memory (analyses, keys, rate limits). All state lost on restart. Needs PostgreSQL or similar.\n4. **Webhook delivery** — `webhook_url` param is accepted but callbacks are never sent\n5. **Wire `recordPayment()`** — x402 payment recording function exists but isn't called from the middleware success path\n\n**Medium-term:**\n6. **Enable x402 payments** — Needs a Base L2 wallet (`X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS`), testnet verification on Base Sepolia, then mainnet flip\n7. **Monitoring/alerting** — No observability beyond the health endpoint\n8. **Load testing** — Not yet performed\n\n### Architecture Notes\n\n- **Stack:** Hono + TypeScript + Node 20, deployed on Railway\n- **Standalone service** — No code-level integration with the main Parse platform (`parse-github`). Separate repo, separate deploy.\n- **3,052 lines** of TypeScript across 12 source files\n- **Source:** `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/`\n\n### Recommended Next Steps (Priority Order)\n\n1. **Commit & deploy** the pending changes (trivial)\n2. **Add PostgreSQL** for persistent API keys, analyses, and rate limits (moderate effort, high impact)\n3. **Implement webhook callbacks** for analysis completion (low effort)\n4. **Set up Base L2 wallet** and test x402 on Sepolia (external dependency)\n5. **Add monitoring** (Sentry, Datadog, or similar)\n\nWant me to start on any of these?\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772766408427}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4bcf815","parentId":"931819b3","timestamp":"2026-03-06T03:06:48.455Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_37513dd6e7e14626bf63a9c3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Task Result\n\n**Task:** Check status of x402 implementation\n\n**Model:** claude-code\n\n---\n\nNow I have the full picture. Here's the x402 implementation status report.\n\n---\n\n## x402 Implementation Status Report\n\n### Summary: Code Complete, Not Live in Production\n\nThe x402 payment integration for **Parse for Agents** (`parse-for-agents`) is **fully coded and deployed** but **disabled in production** — the Railway environment is missing the `X402_ENABLED`, `X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS`, and related environment variables.\n\n---\n\n### What Has Been Built\n\n| Component | File | Status |\n|-----------|------|--------|\n| **x402 middleware** | `src/x402.ts` (96 lines) | Done — uses official `@x402/hono` SDK |\n| **Auth bypass for paid requests** | `src/auth.ts:133-137` | Done — `x402Paid` context flag skips API key check |\n| **Middleware mount** | `src/app.ts:78-80` | Done — guard on `/v1/analyze`, `/v1/evaluate`, `/v1/chat` |\n| **Pricing endpoint** | `GET /v1/pricing` (app.ts:241) | Done — public endpoint returns rates and wallet info |\n| **Payment ledger** | `src/payment-ledger.ts` (53 lines) | Done — in-memory, bounded to 1000 records |\n| **Payment stats endpoint** | `GET /v1/payments/stats` (app.ts:558) | Done — admin-only, returns revenue metrics |\n| **PaymentRecord type** | `src/types.ts:159-168` | Done |\n| **Dashboard x402 section** | `src/dashboard.ts:276+` | Done — code examples for agents |\n| **Quickstart docs** | `docs/quickstart.md:161` | Done — mentions x402 as alternative auth |\n| **NPM dependencies** | `@x402/hono`, `@x402/core`, `@x402/evm` (v2.5.0) | Installed |\n| **Env template** | `.env.example` | Done — X402_* vars documented |\n| **Root endpoint** | `app.ts:108-113` | Done — shows x402 status to agents |\n| **Health check** | `app.ts:123` | Done — reports `x402_enabled` |\n| **Design doc** | `x402-payment-design.md` | Complete — 673 lines, full architecture |\n\n**Pricing configured:**\n- `/v1/analyze`: $0.01 (quick) / $0.05 (standard) / $0.15 (deep)\n- `/v1/evaluate`: $0.01\n- `/v1/chat`: $0.005\n- Currency: USDC on Base L2 (`eip155:8453`)\n\n---\n\n### What Remains\n\n| Task | Blocker | Priority |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| **Set up Base L2 wallet** | Need a Coinbase Smart Wallet / EOA to receive USDC | **Critical** |\n| **Set Railway env vars** | `X402_ENABLED=true`, `X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS=0x...` not set | **Critical** |\n| **Testnet validation** | No evidence of end-to-end test with `purl` or `@x402/fetch` | High |\n| **Payment recording hook** | `recordPayment()` is defined but never called from x402 middleware — payments are verified but not logged to the ledger | High |\n| **Dynamic depth pricing** | Current middleware uses a single price for `/v1/analyze` ($0.05). Quick/deep depths aren't differentiated at the x402 layer | Medium |\n| **Persistent storage** | Ledger is in-memory; payments lost on restart | Low (Phase 2) |\n\n---\n\n### Blockers\n\n1. **No wallet address**: The `X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS` is empty. Someone needs to create/designate a Base L2 wallet to receive USDC payments.\n\n2. **Payment ledger not wired**: The `x402Guard()` middleware marks `x402Paid=true` on the context but doesn't call `recordPayment()` — so even when enabled, payments won't appear in the stats endpoint or ledger.\n\n3. **No end-to-end test**: The code compiles and the middleware structure is correct, but there's no evidence it's been tested against the facilitator (even on Base Sepolia testnet).\n\n---\n\n### Earlier Prototype (Archived)\n\nAn earlier custom x402 implementation exists at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/_exiled/src/lib/x402/` (custom validation, mock payment, email-style wallet addresses). This has been superseded by the official SDK approach in `parse-for-agents`. No action needed on the prototype.\n\n---\n\n### Bottom Line\n\nThe x402 integration is **~85% complete**. The code is solid and uses the official SDK correctly. To go live:\n\n1. Create a Base L2 wallet and set `X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS` + `X402_ENABLED=true` in Railway\n2. Wire `recordPayment()` into the x402 middleware callback\n3. Test on Base Sepolia before switching to mainnet\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772766408446}}
