{"type":"message","id":"6c5d68a3","parentId":"de1b226e","timestamp":"2026-03-06T03:08:07.297Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2dd1eb7124ab413ebb7cc80e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ntask_id: high-1772671400\npriority: high\ncreated: 2026-03-05T19:10:00-05:00\nsource: hourly-reflection\n---\n\n# Task: Apply Watchdog False-Positive Fix\n\n## Objective\nApply the 3-line fix to eliminate 35 false-positive stalled_warnings.\n\n## Bug Location\nFile: `scripts/ogedei-watchdog.py`\nLine: ~140\n\n## Fix\n```python\n# Current (buggy):\nif \".executing\" in f.name and f.is_file():\n\n# Fix:\nname = f.name\nif \".executing\" in name and \".completed\" not in name and \".done\" not in name and \".failed\" not in name and f.is_file():\n```\n\n## Root Cause\nThe string `.executing` matches completed task files like `.executing.completed.done`, incorrectly flagging them as stalled.\n\n## Success Criteria\n1. Edit the file successfully\n2. Run `python3 scripts/ogedei-watchdog.py --once` to verify\n3. Confirm stalled_warnings drops to 0 (for real stalled tasks only)\n\n## Blocker\nWrite permission to scripts/ directory may be denied. If blocked, escalate to Kublai with:\n- Fix details\n- Permission request\n- Impact statement (35 false positives eliminated)\n\n## Context\nOgedei has had this fix ready for 3 reflection cycles. Time to ship it.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772766487296}}
