{"type":"message","id":"1456c154","parentId":"e7d1b851","timestamp":"2026-03-06T03:08:56.882Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture. All four tasks were created at 2026-03-05T19:10:00-05:00 (7:10 PM EST). It's now 10:07 PM EST, so they've been pending for about 2 hours and 57 minutes - just under 3 hours.\n\nThe HEARTBEAT.md says to check for \"agents blocked >4 hours\" - these aren't quite at 4 hours yet, but they're getting close.\n\nHowever, looking at the tasks:\n\n1. **ogedei: Watchdog fix** - Simple 3-line fix, permission issue. This is actionable.\n2. **mongke: x402 validation** - Research task, Mongke \"failed to deliver\" at 6:02 PM\n3. **temujin: Parse for Agents MVP** - BLOCKED for 18+ hours on filesystem access\n4. **jochi: Fleet utilization report** - Analysis task\n\nThe temujin task is interesting - it says \"18+ hours\" blocked. That's definitely >4 hours.\n\nFor the Self-Direction part of the heartbeat:\n1. Review results since last heartbeat - I just handled an x402 status query\n2. What do I want to do? - These pending tasks need attention\n3. Review goals from MEMORY.md - Mission is financial liberation through AI coordination\n4. Identify proactive actions - The watchdog fix is simple and actionable, temujin has been blocked for 18+ hours\n\nLooking at this:\n- ogedei has a simple 3-line fix that's been ready\n- temujin has been blocked for 18+ hours on filesystem access\n- mongke failed to deliver on x402 validation\n- jochi has a fleet analysis task\n\nThe HEARTBEAT.md says \"If something calls to me -> route it to the right specialist (NEVER self-execute specialist work)\"\n\nActually, wait - the ogedei task is to fix ogedei-watchdog.py. But that's ogedei's own script. I shouldn't fix it myself, I should route it... but it's already routed to ogedei.\n\nLooking more carefully - these tasks are already assigned to agents. They're just stuck. The ogedei task is about applying a fix